.IX Title "SMOKETRACE 7"
.TH SMOKETRACE 7 "2008-06-09" "2.4.0" "SmokePing"
.SH "NAME"
SmokeTrace \- Ajax based Traceroute for Smokeping
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
SmokeTraceoute is an browser based traceroute application written in the
Qooxdoo. You can easily activate it in your Smokeping setup, to allow
users to traceroute smokeping targets directly from the master host.
.SH "SETUP"
.IX Header "SETUP"
To activate SmokeTrace you just have to copy a few files:
.IP "1." 4
Copy \fIhtdocs/script/Tr.js\fR to your smokeping web directory.
.IP "2." 4
Copy and edit \fIhtdocs/tr.html\fR to your smokeping web directory. Make
sure the path to \fITr.js\fR is correct.
.IP "3." 4
Copy \fIhtdocs/resource\fR into the directory where you put \fItr.html\fR.
.IP "4." 4
Copy and edit \fIhtdocs/tr.cgi.dist\fR to the directory where you put
\&\fItr.html\fR and change its name to \fItr.cgi\fR. Make sure \fItr.cgi\fR to adjust
the \fIuse lib\fR line to point to the smokeping per lib directory, as you did
with \fIsmokeping.cgi\fR. Make sure the webserver actually executes the
\&\fItr.cgi\fR script.
.IP "5." 4
Edit your config file and add the line:
.Sp
.Vb 4
\& menuextra = <a target=\(aq_blank\(aq href=\(aqtr.html{HOST}\(aq class=\(aq{CLASS}\(aq \e
\&    onclick="window.open(this.href,this.target, \e
\&    \(aqwidth=800,height=500,toolbar=no,location=no,status=no,scrollbars=no\(aq); \e
\&    return false;">*</a>
.Ve
.Sp
to your \fI*** Targets ***\fR section. It will make a '*' appear next to each
host name, and when you click on it, the SmokeTrace window will open.
